headline: Jacobs tops quarterly estimates on strong demand for professional services
summary: Engineering services firm Jacobs Solutions beat Wall Street estimates for third-quarter profit and revenue on Tuesday, boosted by steady demand in its Infrastructure and Advanced Facilities (I&AF) as well as PA Consulting segments. Sustained demand for its professional services shielded the Dallas, Texas-based company from macroeconomic uncertainty amid an inflationary market and the ongoing global tariff war. "This strong performance was fueled by higher revenue growth rates in both segments as well as disciplined cost control," CFO Venk Nathamuni said.

headline: Jacobs Solutions (NYSE:J) Misses Q2 Revenue Estimates
summary: Global professional services company Jacobs Solutions (NYSE:J) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, but sales rose 5.2% year on year to $3.03 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.62 per share was 5.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
